b(32, 33, 34); font-weight: 700;">Python</span><span style="font-size: calc(0.875em); color: rgb(32, 33, 34);">&nbsp;is an&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interpreted_language" title="Interpreted language" style="font-size: calc(0.875em); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">interpreted</a><span style="font-size: calc(0.875em); color: rgb(32, 33, 34);">,&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/High-level_programming_language" title="High-level programming language" style="font-size: calc(0.875em); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">high-level</a><span style="font-size: calc(0.875em); color: rgb(32, 33, 34);">,&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/General-purpose_programming_language" title="General-purpose programming language" style="font-size: calc(0.875em); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">general-purpose</a><span style="font-size: calc(0.875em); color: rgb(32, 33, 34);">&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Programming_language" title="Programming language" style="font-size: calc(0.875em); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">programming language</a><span style="font-size: calc(0.875em); color: rgb(32, 33, 34);">. Created by&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guido_van_Rossum" title="Guido van Rossum" style="font-size: calc(0.875em); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Guido van Rossum</a><span style="font-size: calc(0.875em); color: rgb(32, 33, 34);">&nbsp;and first released in 1991, Python's design philosophy emphasizes&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Code_readability" class="mw-redirect" title="Code readability" style="font-size: calc(0.875em); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">code readability</a><span style="font-size: calc(0.875em); color: rgb(32, 33, 34);">&nbsp;with its notable use of&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Off-side_rule" title="Off-side rule" style="font-size: calc(0.875em); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">significant whitespace</a><span style="font-size: calc(0.875em); color: rgb(32, 33, 34);">. Its&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Language_construct" title="Language construct" style="font-size: calc(0.875em); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">language constructs</a><span style="font-size: calc(0.875em); color: rgb(32, 33, 34);">&nbsp;and&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Object-oriented_programming" title="Object-oriented programming" style="font-size: calc(0.875em); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">object-oriented</a><span style="font-size: calc(0.875em); color: rgb(32, 33, 34);">&nbsp;approach aim to help programmers write clear, logical code for small and large-scale projects.</span><sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-7_28-0" class="reference" style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-7-28" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); text-decoration-line: underline;">[28]</a></sup></div><div id="content" class="mw-body" role="main" style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34); padding: 1.25em 1.5em 1.5em; direction: ltr; border-width: 1px 0px 1px 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(167, 215, 249); border-image: initial; margin-top: -1px; margin-left: 11em; font-size: 16px;"><div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content" style="font-size: calc(0.875em); line-height: 1.6; position: relative; z-index: 0;"><div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr" style="direction: ltr;"><div class="mw-parser-output"><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Python is&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dynamic_programming_language" title="Dynamic programming language" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">dynamically typed</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Garbage_collection_(computer_science)" title="Garbage collection (computer science)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">garbage-collected</a>. It supports multiple&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Programming_paradigms" class="mw-redirect" title="Programming paradigms" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">programming paradigms</a>, including&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Structured_programming" title="Structured programming" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">structured</a>&nbsp;(particularly,&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Procedural_programming" title="Procedural programming" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">procedural</a>), object-oriented, and&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Functional_programming" title="Functional programming" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">functional programming</a>. Python is often described as a "batteries included" language due to its comprehensive&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Standard_library" title="Standard library" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">standard library</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-About_29-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-About-29" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[29]</a></sup></p><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Python was conceived in the late 1980s as a successor to the&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ABC_(programming_language)" title="ABC (programming language)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">ABC language</a>. Python&nbsp;2.0, released in 2000, introduced features like&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_comprehension" title="List comprehension" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">list comprehensions</a>&nbsp;and a garbage collection system capable of collecting&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reference_cycle" class="mw-redirect" title="Reference cycle" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">reference cycles</a>. Python&nbsp;3.0, released in 2008, was a major revision of the language that is not completely&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Backward_compatibility" title="Backward compatibility" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">backward-compatible</a>, and much Python&nbsp;2 code does not run unmodified on Python&nbsp;3.</p><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">The Python&nbsp;2 language was officially discontinued in 2020 (first planned for 2015), and "Python 2.7.18 is the last Python 2.7 release and therefore the last Python 2 release."<sup id="cite_ref-30" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-30" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[30]</a></sup>&nbsp;No more security patches or other improvements will be released for it.<sup id="cite_ref-31" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-31" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[31]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-32" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-32" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[32]</a></sup>&nbsp;With Python 2's&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/End-of-life_(product)" title="End-of-life (product)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">end-of-life</a>, only Python&nbsp;3.5.x<sup id="cite_ref-33" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-33" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[33]</a></sup>&nbsp;and later are supported.</p><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Python&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interpreter_(computing)" title="Interpreter (computing)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">interpreters</a>&nbsp;are available for many&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Operating_system" title="Operating system" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">operating systems</a>. A global community of programmers develops and maintains&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CPython" title="CPython" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">CPython</a>, an&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open-source_software" title="Open-source software" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">open source</a><sup id="cite_ref-34" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-34" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[34]</a></sup>&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reference_implementation" title="Reference implementation" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">reference implementation</a>. A&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nonprofit_organization" title="Nonprofit organization" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">non-profit organization</a>, the&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_Software_Foundation" title="Python Software Foundation" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Python Software Foundation</a>, manages and directs resources for Python and CPython development.</p><div id="toc" class="toc" role="navigation" aria-labelledby="mw-toc-heading" style="border: 1px solid rgb(162, 169, 177); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); padding: 7px; font-size: 13.3px; display: table;"><div class="toctitle" lang="en" dir="ltr" style="text-align: center; direction: ltr;"><h2 id="mw-toc-heading" style="font-family: sans-serif; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.3; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 1em 0px 0.25em; font-size: 13.3px; background: none; overflow: hidden; padding: 0px; border: 0px; display: inline;">Contents</h2><span class="toctogglespan" style="font-size: 12.502px;"><label class="toctogglelabel" for="toctogglecheckbox" style="cursor: pointer; color: rgb(6, 69, 173);"></label></span></div><ul style="margin: 0.3em 0px; list-style-image: none; padding: 0px; list-style-type: none;"><li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-1" style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#History" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);"><span class="tocnumber" style="display: table-cell; text-decoration: inherit; color: rgb(32, 33, 34); padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0.5em;">1</span><span class="toctext" style="display: table-cell; text-decoration: 