rgin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; white-space: nowrap; unicode-bidi: isolate;"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket" style="margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);">[</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Python_(programming_language)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9" title="Edit section: Mathematics" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket" style="margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);">]</span></span></h3><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Python has the usual symbols for arithmetic operators (<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">+</code>,&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">-</code>,&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">*</code>,&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">/</code>), the floor division operator&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">//</code>&nbsp;and the&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Modulo_operation" title="Modulo operation" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">remainder operator</a>&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">%</code>&nbsp;(where the remainder can be negative, e.g.&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">4&nbsp;% -3 == -2</code>). It also has&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">**</code>&nbsp;for&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Exponentiation" title="Exponentiation" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">exponentiation</a>, e.g.&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">5**3 == 125</code>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">9**0.5 == 3.0</code>, and a matrix multiply operator&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">@</code>&nbsp;.<sup id="cite_ref-88" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-88" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[88]</a></sup>&nbsp;These operators work like in traditional math; with the same&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Order_of_operations" title="Order of operations" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">precedence rules</a>, the operators&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infix_notation" title="Infix notation" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">infix</a>&nbsp;(&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">+</code>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">-</code>&nbsp;can also be&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unary_operation" title="Unary operation" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">unary</a>&nbsp;to represent positive and negative numbers respectively).</p><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Division between integers produces floating point results. The behavior of division has changed significantly over time:<sup id="cite_ref-pep0238_89-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-pep0238-89" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[89]</a></sup></p><ul style="margin: 0.3em 0px 0px 1.6em; list-style-image: url(&quot;/w/skins/Vector/resources/skins.vector.styles/images/bullet-icon.svg?d4515&quot;); padding: 0px;"><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;">Python 2.1 and earlier used C's division behavior. The&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">/</code>&nbsp;operator is integer division if both operands are integers, and floating-point division otherwise. Integer division rounds towards 0, e.g.&nbsp;<span class="nowrap" style="white-space: nowrap;"><code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">7/3 == 2</code></span>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<span class="nowrap" style="white-space: nowrap;"><code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">-7/3 == -2</code>.</span></li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;">Python 2.2 changed integer division to round towards negative infinity, e.g.&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">7/3 == 2</code>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">-7/3 == -3</code>. The floor division&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">//</code>&nbsp;operator was introduced. So&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">7//3 == 2</code>,&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">-7//3 == -3</code>,&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">7.5//3 == 2.0</code>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">-7.5//3 == -3.0</code>. Adding&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">from __future__ import division</code>&nbsp;causes a module to use Python 3.0 rules for division (see next).</li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;">Python 3.0 changed&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">/</code>&nbsp;to always be floating-point division, e.g.&nbsp;<span class="nowrap" style="white-space: nowrap;"><code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">5/2 == 2.5</code></span>.</li></ul><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">In Python terms,&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">/</code>&nbsp;is&nbsp;<i>true division</i>&nbsp;(or simply&nbsp;<i>division</i>), and&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">//</code>&nbsp;is&nbsp;<i>floor division.</i>&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">/</code>&nbsp;before version 3.0 is&nbsp;<i>classic division</i>.<sup id="cite_ref-pep0238_89-1" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-pep0238-89" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[89]</a></sup></p><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Rounding towards negative infinity, though different from most languages, adds consistency. For instance, it means that the equation&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">(a + b)//b == a//b + 1</code>&nbsp;is always true. It also means that the equation&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">b*(a//b) + a%b == a</code>&nbsp;is valid for both positive and negative values of&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">a</code>. However, maintaining the validity of this equation means that while the result of&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">a%b</code>&nbsp;is, as expected, in the&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Half-open_interval" class="mw-redirect" title="Half-open interval" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">half-open interval</a>&nbsp;[0,&nbsp;<i>b</i>), where&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">b</code>&nbsp;is a positive integer, it has to lie in the interval (<i>b</i>, 0] when&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">b</code>&nbsp;is negative.<sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-62_90-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-62-90" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[90]</a></sup></p><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Python provides a&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">round</code>&nbsp;function for&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rounding" title="Rounding" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">rounding</a>&nbsp;a float to the nearest integer. For&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rounding#Tie-breaking" title="Rounding" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">tie-breaking</a>, Python 3 uses&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Round_to_even" class="mw-redirect" title="Round to even" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">round to even</a>:&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">round(1.5)</code>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">round(2.5)</code>&nbsp;both produce&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">2</code>.<sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-64_91-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-64-91" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[91]</a></sup>&nbsp;Versions before 3 used&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rounding#Rounding_away_from_zero" title="Rounding" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">round-away-from-zero</a>:&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">round(0.5)</code>&nbsp;is&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">1.0</code>,&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">round(-0.5)</code>&nbsp;is&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">‚àí1.0</code>.<sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-63_92-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-63-92" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[92]</a></sup></p><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Python allows boolean expressions with multiple equality relations in a manner that is consistent with general use in mathematics. For example, the expression&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">a &lt; b &lt; c</code>&nbsp;tests whether&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">a</code>&nbsp;is less than&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">b</code>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">b</code>&nbsp;is less than&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">c</code>.<sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-65_93-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-65-93" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[93]</a></sup>&nbsp;C-derived languages interpret this expression differently: in C, the expression would first evaluate&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">a &lt; b</code>, resulting in 0 or 1, and that result would then be compared with&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">c</code>.<sup id="cite_ref-CPL_94-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-CPL-94" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[94]</a></sup></p><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Python uses&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arbitrary-precision_arithmetic" title="Arbitrary-precision arithmetic" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">arbitrary-precision arithmetic</a>&nbsp;for all integer operations. The&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">Decimal</code>&nbsp;type/class in the&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">decimal</code>&nbsp;module provides decimal floating point numbers to a pre-defined arbitrary precision and several rounding modes.<sup id="cite_ref-95" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-95" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[95]</a></sup>&nbsp;The&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">Fraction</code>&nbsp;class in the&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">fractions</code>&nbsp;module provides arbitrary precision for&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rational_number" title="Rational number" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">rational numbers</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-96" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-96" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[96]</a></sup></p><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Due to Python's extensive mathematics library, and the third-party library&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NumPy" title="NumPy" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">NumPy</a>&nbsp;that further extends the native capabilities, it is frequently used as a scientific scripting language to aid in problems such as numerical data processing and manipulation.<sup id="cite_ref-97" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-97" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[97]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-98" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-98" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[98]</a></sup></p><h2 style="font-family: &quot;Linux Libertine&quot;, Georgia, Times, serif; line-height: 1.3; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 1em 0px 0.25em; font-size: 1.5em; background: none; overflow: hidden; padding: 0px; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(162, 169, 177);"><span class="mw-headline" id="Python_programming_examples">Python programming examples</span><span class="mw-editsection" style="font-family: sans-serif; user-select: none; font-size: small; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; white-space: nowrap; unicode-bidi: isolate;"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket" style="margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);">[</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Python_(programming_language)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10" title="Edit section: Python programming examples" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket" style="margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);">]</span></span></h2><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%22Hello,_World!%22_program" title="&quot;Hello, World!&quot; program" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Hello world</a>&nbsp;program:</p><div class="mw-highlight mw-highlight-lang-python mw-content-ltr" dir="ltr" style="background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: inherit; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed;"><pre style="overflow-x: hidden; font-family: monospace, monospace; padding: 1em; line-height: 1.3; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-color: rgb(234, 236, 240); white-space: pre-wrap; tab-size: 4;"><span class="nb" style="color: rgb(0, 128, 0);">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1" style="color: rgb(186, 33, 33);">'Hello, world!'</span><span class="p">)</span>\r\n</pre></div><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Program to calculate the&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Factorial" title="Factorial" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">factorial</a>&nbsp;of a positive integer:</p><div class="mw-highlight mw-highlight-lang-python mw-content-ltr" dir="ltr" style="background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: inherit; direction: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed;"><pre style="overflow-x: hidden; font-family: monospace, monospace; padding: 1em; line-height: 1.3; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-color: rgb(234, 236, 240); white-space: pre-wrap; tab-size: 4;"><span class="n">n</span> <span class="o" style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);">=</span> <span class="nb" style="color: rgb(0, 128, 0);">int</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nb" style="color: rgb(0, 128, 0);">input</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1" style="color: rgb(186, 33, 33);">'Type a number, and its factorial will be printed: '</span><span class="p">))</span>\r\n\r\n<span class="k" style="color: rgb(0, 128, 0); font-weight: bold;">if</span> <span class="n">n</span> <span class="o" style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);">&lt;</span> <span class="mi" style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);">0</span><span class="p">:</span>\r\n    <span class="k" style="color: rgb(0, 128, 0); font-weight: bold;">raise</span> <span class="ne" style="color: rgb(210, 65, 58); font-weight: bold;">ValueError</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1" style="color: rgb(186, 33, 33);">'You must enter a positive integer'</span><span class="p">)</span>\r\n\r\n<span class="n">fact</span> <span class="o" style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);">=</span> <span class="mi" style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);">1</span>\r\n<span class="n">i</span> <span class="o" style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);">=</span> <span class="mi" style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);">2</span>\r\n<span class="k" style="color: rgb(0, 128, 0); font-weight: bold;">while</span> <span class="n">i</span> <span class="o" style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);">&lt;=</span> <span class="n">n</span><span class="p">:</span>\r\n    <span class="n">fact</span> <span class="o" style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);">*=</span> <span class="n">i</span>\r\n    <span class="n">i</span> <span class="o" style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);">+=</span> <span class="mi" style="color: rgb(102, 102, 102);">1</span>\r\n\r\n<span class="nb" style="color: rgb(0, 128, 0);">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">fact</span><span class="p">)</span>\r\n</pre></div><h2 style="font-family: &quot;Linux Libertine&quot;, Georgia, Times, serif; line-height: 1.3; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 1em 0px 0.25em; font-size: 1.5em; background: none; overflow: hidden; padding: 0px; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(162, 169, 177);"><span class="mw-headline" id="Libraries">Libraries</span><span class="mw-editsection" style="font-family: sans-serif; user-select: none; font-size: small; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; white-space: nowrap; unicode-bidi: isolate;"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket" style="margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);">[</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Python_(programming_language)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11" title="Edit section: Libraries" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket" style="margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);">]</span></span></h2><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Python's large&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Standard_library" title="Standard library" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">standard library</a>, commonly cited as one of its greatest strengths,<sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-86_99-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-86-99" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[99]</a></sup>&nbsp;provides tools suited to many tasks. For Internet-facing applications, many standard formats and protocols such as&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MIME" title="MIME" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">MIME</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hypertext_Transfer_Protocol" title="Hypertext Transfer Protocol" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">HTTP</a>&nbsp;are supported. It includes modules for creating&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Graphical_user_interface" title="Graphical user interface" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">graphical user interfaces</a>, connecting to&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Relational_database" title="Relational database" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">relational databases</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pseudorandom_number_generator" title="Pseudorandom number generator" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">generating pseudorandom numbers</a>, arithmetic with arbitrary-precision decimals,<sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-88_100-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-88-100" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[100]</a></sup>&nbsp;manipulating&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Regular_expression" title="Regular expression" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">regular expressions</a>, and&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unit_testing" title="Unit testing" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">unit testing</a>.</p><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Some parts of the standard library are covered by specifications (for example, the&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Web_Server_Gateway_Interface" title="Web Server Gateway Interface" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Web Server Gateway Interface</a>&nbsp;(WSGI) implementation&nbsp;<code style="font-family: monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.6px; padding-top: 1px; padding-bottom: 1px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); border-radius: 2px; border: 1px solid rgb(234, 236, 240);">wsgiref</code>&nbsp;follows PEP 333<sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-89_101-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-89-101" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[101]</a></sup>), but most modules are not. They are specified by their code, internal documentation, and test suites. However, because most of the standard library is cross-platform Python code, only a few modules need altering or rewriting for variant implementations.</p><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">As of November&nbsp;2019,&nbsp;the&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_Package_Index" title="Python Package Index" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Python Package Index</a>&nbsp;(PyPI), the official repository for third-party Python software, contains over 200,000<sup id="cite_ref-102" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-102" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[102]</a></sup>&nbsp;packages with a wide range of functionality, including:</p><ul style="margin: 0.3em 0px 0px 1.6em; list-style-image: url(&quot;/w/skins/Vector/resources/skins.vector.styles/images/bullet-icon.svg?d4515&quot;); padding: 0px;"><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Automation" title="Automation" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Automation</a></li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Data_analytics" class="mw-redirect" title="Data analytics" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Data analytics</a></li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Databases" class="mw-redirect" title="Databases" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Databases</a></li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;">Documentation</li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Graphical_user_interfaces" class="mw-redirect" title="Graphical user interfaces" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Graphical user interfaces</a></li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Image_processing" class="mw-redirect" title="Image processing" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Image processing</a></li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Machine_learning" title="Machine learning" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Machine learning</a></li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mobile_App" class="mw-redirect" title="Mobile App" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Mobile App</a></li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Multimedia" title="Multimedia" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Multimedia</a></li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;">Networking</li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scientific_computing" class="mw-redirect" title="Scientific computing" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Scientific computing</a></li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/System_administration" class="mw-redirect" title="System administration" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">System administration</a></li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Test_framework" class="mw-redirect" title="Test framework" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Test frameworks</a></li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Text_processing" title="Text processing" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Text processing</a></li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Web_framework" title="Web framework" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Web frameworks</a></li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Web_scraping" title="Web scraping" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Web scraping</a><sup id="cite_ref-103" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-103" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[103]</a></sup></li></ul><h2 style="font-family: &quot;Linux Libertine&quot;, Georgia, Times, serif; line-height: 1.3; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 1em 0px 0.25em; font-size: 1.5em; background: none; overflow: hidden; padding: 0px; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(162, 169, 177);"><span class="mw-headline" id="Development_environments">Development environments</span><span class="mw-editsection" style="font-family: sans-serif; user-select: none; font-size: small; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; white-space: nowrap; unicode-bidi: isolate;"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket" style="margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);">[</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Python_(programming_language)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=12" title="Edit section: Development environments" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket" style="margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);">]</span></span></h2><div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable" style="font-style: italic; padding-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">See also:&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Comparison_of_integrated_development_environments#Python" title="Comparison of integrated development environments" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Comparison of integrated development environments ¬ß&nbsp;Python</a></div><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Most Python implementations (including CPython) include a&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Read%E2%80%93eval%E2%80%93print_loop" title="Read‚Äìeval‚Äìprint loop" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">read‚Äìeval‚Äìprint loop</a>&nbsp;(REPL), permitting them to function as a&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Command_line_interpreter" class="mw-redirect" title="Command line interpreter" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">command line interpreter</a>&nbsp;for which the user enters statements sequentially and receives results immediately.</p><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Other shells, including&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IDLE" title="IDLE" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">IDLE</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IPython" title="IPython" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">IPython</a>, add further abilities such as improved auto-completion, session state retention and&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syntax_highlighting" title="Syntax highlighting" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">syntax highlighting</a>.</p><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">As well as standard desktop&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Integrated_development_environment" title="Integrated development environment" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">integrated development environments</a>, there are&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Web_browser" title="Web browser" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Web browser</a>-based IDEs;&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SageMath" title="SageMath" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">SageMath</a>&nbsp;(intended for developing science and math-related Python programs);&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PythonAnywhere" title="PythonAnywhere" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">PythonAnywhere</a>, a browser-based IDE and hosting environment; and Canopy IDE, a commercial Python IDE emphasizing&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scientific_computing" class="mw-redirect" title="Scientific computing" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">scientific computing</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-104" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-104" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[104]</a></sup></p><h2 style="font-family: &quot;Linux Libertine&quot;, Georgia, Times, serif; line-height: 1.3; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 1em 0px 0.25em; font-size: 1.5em; background: none; overflow: hidden; padding: 0px; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(162, 169, 177);"><span class="mw-headline" id="Implementations">Implementations</span><span class="mw-editsection" style="font-family: sans-serif; user-select: none; font-size: small; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; white-space: nowrap; unicode-bidi: isolate;"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket" style="margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);">[</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Python_(programming_language)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=13" title="Edit section: Implementations" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket" style="margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);">]</span></span></h2><div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable" style="font-style: italic; padding-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">See also:&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Python_software#Python_implementations" title="List of Python software" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">List of Python software ¬ß&nbsp;Python implementations</a></div><h3 style="font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.6; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 0.3em 0px 0px; font-size: 1.2em; background: none; overflow: hidden; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; border-bottom: 0px;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Reference_implementation">Reference implementation</span><span class="mw-editsection" style="user-select: none; font-size: small; font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; white-space: nowrap; unicode-bidi: isolate;"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket" style="margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);">[</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Python_(programming_language)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=14" title="Edit section: Reference implementation" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket" style="margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);">]</span></span></h3><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CPython" title="CPython" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">CPython</a>&nbsp;is the&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reference_implementation" title="Reference implementation" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">reference implementation</a>&nbsp;of Python. It is written in&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/C_(programming_language)" title="C (programming language)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">C</a>, meeting the&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/C89_(C_version)" class="mw-redirect" title="C89 (C version)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">C89</a>&nbsp;standard with several select&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/C99" title="C99" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">C99</a>&nbsp;features.<sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-66_105-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-66-105" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[105]</a></sup>&nbsp;It compiles Python programs into an intermediate&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bytecode" title="Bytecode" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">bytecode</a><sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-67_106-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-67-106" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[106]</a></sup>&nbsp;which is then executed by its&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Virtual_machine" title="Virtual machine" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">virtual machine</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-68_107-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-68-107" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[107]</a></sup>&nbsp;CPython is distributed with a large standard library written in a mixture of C and native Python. It is available for many platforms, including&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Microsoft_Windows" title="Microsoft Windows" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Windows</a>&nbsp;(Vista and later; supported&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Windows_XP" title="Windows XP" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Windows XP</a>&nbsp;and older, with by now unsupported Python 2.7) and most modern&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unix-like" title="Unix-like" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Unix-like</a>&nbsp;systems. Platform portability was one of its earliest priorities,<sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-69_108-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-69-108" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[108]</a></sup>&nbsp;in Python 1 and 2 time-frame, even supporting&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OpenVMS" title="OpenVMS" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">VMS</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OS/2" title="OS/2" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">OS/2</a>, while since support has been dropped for a lot of platforms.</p><h3 style="font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.6; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 0.3em 0px 0px; font-size: 1.2em; background: none; overflow: hidden; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; border-bottom: 0px;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Other_implementations">Other implementations</span><span class="mw-editsection" style="user-select: none; font-size: small; font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; white-space: nowrap; unicode-bidi: isolate;"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket" style="margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);">[</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Python_(programming_language)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=15" title="Edit section: Other implementations" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket" style="margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);">]</span></span></h3><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PyPy" title="PyPy" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">PyPy</a>&nbsp;is a fast, compliant interpreter of Python 2.7 and 3.6.<sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-70_109-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-70-109" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[109]</a></sup>&nbsp;Its&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Just-in-time_compilation" title="Just-in-time compilation" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">just-in-time compiler</a>&nbsp;brings a significant speed improvement over CPython but several libraries written in C cannot be used with it.<sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-71_110-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-71-110" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[110]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-111" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-111" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[111]</a></sup></p><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stackless_Python" title="Stackless Python" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Stackless Python</a>&nbsp;is a significant fork of CPython that implements&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Microthread" title="Microthread" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">microthreads</a>; it does not use the C memory stack, thus allowing massively concurrent programs. PyPy also has a stackless version.<sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-73_112-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-73-112" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[112]</a></sup></p><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MicroPython" title="MicroPython" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">MicroPython</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CircuitPython" title="CircuitPython" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">CircuitPython</a>&nbsp;are Python 3 variants optimized for&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Microcontroller" title="Microcontroller" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">microcontrollers</a>. This includes&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lego_Mindstorms_EV3" title="Lego Mindstorms EV3" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Lego Mindstorms EV3</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-113" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-113" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[113]</a></sup></p><h3 style="font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.6; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 0.3em 0px 0px; font-size: 1.2em; background: none; overflow: hidden; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; border-bottom: 0px;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Unsupported_implementations">Unsupported implementations</span><span class="mw-editsection" style="user-select: none; font-size: small; font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; white-space: nowrap; unicode-bidi: isolate;"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket" style="margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);">[</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Python_(programming_language)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=16" title="Edit section: Unsupported implementations" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket" style="margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);">]</span></span></h3><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Other just-in-time Python compilers have been developed, but are now unsupported:</p><ul style="margin: 0.3em 0px 0px 1.6em; list-style-image: url(&quot;/w/skins/Vector/resources/skins.vector.styles/images/bullet-icon.svg?d4515&quot;); padding: 0px;"><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;">Google began a project named&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unladen_Swallow" class="mw-redirect" title="Unladen Swallow" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Unladen Swallow</a>&nbsp;in 2009, with the aim of speeding up the Python interpreter five-fold by using the&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LLVM" title="LLVM" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">LLVM</a>, and of improving its multithreading ability to scale to thousands of cores,<sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-74_114-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-74-114" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[114]</a></sup>&nbsp;while ordinary implementations suffer from the&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Global_interpreter_lock" title="Global interpreter lock" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">global interpreter lock</a>.</li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Psyco" title="Psyco" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Psyco</a>&nbsp;was a&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Just-in-time_compilation" title="Just-in-time compilation" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">just-in-time</a>&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Run-time_algorithm_specialization" title="Run-time algorithm specialization" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">specializing</a>&nbsp;compiler that integrates with CPython and transforms bytecode to machine code at runtime. The emitted code is specialized for certain&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Data_type" title="Data type" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">data types</a>&nbsp;and is faster than standard Python code.</li></ul><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">In 2005,&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nokia" title="Nokia" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Nokia</a>&nbsp;released a Python interpreter for the&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Series_60" class="mw-redirect" title="Series 60" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Series 60</a>&nbsp;mobile phones named&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PyS60" class="mw-redirect" title="PyS60" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">PyS60</a>. It includes many of the modules from the CPython implementations and some additional modules to integrate with the&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Symbian" title="Symbian" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Symbian</a>&nbsp;operating system. The project has been kept up-to-date to run on all variants of the S60 platform, and several third-party modules are available. The Nokia&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/N900" class="mw-redirect" title="N900" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">N900</a>&nbsp;also supports Python with&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GTK" title="GTK" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">GTK</a>&nbsp;widget libraries, enabling programs to be written and run on the target device.<sup id="cite_ref-115" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-115" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[115]</a></sup></p><h3 style="font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.6; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 0.3em 0px 0px; font-size: 1.2em; background: none; overflow: hidden; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; border-bottom: 0px;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Cross-compilers_to_other_languages">Cross-compilers to other languages</span><span class="mw-editsection" style="user-select: none; font-size: small; font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; white-space: nowrap; unicode-bidi: isolate;"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket" style="margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);">[</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Python_(programming_language)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=17" title="Edit section: Cross-compilers to other languages" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket" style="margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);">]</span></span></h3><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">There are several compilers to high-level&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Object_language" title="Object language" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">object languages</a>, with either unrestricted Python, a restricted subset of Python, or a language similar to Python as the source language:</p><ul style="margin: 0.3em 0px 0px 1.6em; list-style-image: url(&quot;/w/skins/Vector/resources/skins.vector.styles/images/bullet-icon.svg?d4515&quot;); padding: 0px;"><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cython" title="Cython" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Cython</a>&nbsp;compiles Python to&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/C_(programming_language)" title="C (programming language)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">C</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/C%2B%2B" title="C++" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">C++</a>.</li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;">Google's Grumpy compiles Python to&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Go_(programming_language)" title="Go (programming language)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Go</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-116" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-116" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[116]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-117" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-117" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[117]</a></sup></li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IronPython" title="IronPython" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">IronPython</a>&nbsp;follows a similar approach in order to run Python programs on the .NET&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Common_Language_Runtime" title="Common Language Runtime" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Common Language Runtime</a>.</li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jython" title="Jython" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Jython</a>&nbsp;enables the use of the Java class library from a Python program.</li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MyHDL" title="MyHDL" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">MyHDL</a>&nbsp;compiles Python to&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/VHDL" title="VHDL" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">VHDL</a>.</li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nuitka" title="Nuitka" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Nuitka</a>&nbsp;compiles Python into C++.<sup id="cite_ref-118" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-118" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[118]</a></sup></li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Numba" title="Numba" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Numba</a>&nbsp;uses&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LLVM" title="LLVM" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">LLVM</a>&nbsp;to compile Python to machine code.</li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pyjs" title="Pyjs" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Pyjs</a>&nbsp;compiles Python to&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/JavaScript" title="JavaScript" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">JavaScript</a>.</li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pyrex_(programming_language)" title="Pyrex (programming language)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Pyrex</a>&nbsp;(latest release in 2010) and&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shed_Skin" title="Shed Skin" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Shed Skin</a>&nbsp;(latest release in 2013) compile to C and C++ respectively.</li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;">Pythran compiles Python to&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/C%2B%2B" title="C++" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">C++</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-119" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-119" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[119]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-120" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-120" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[120]</a></sup></li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/RPython" class="mw-redirect" title="RPython" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">RPython</a>&nbsp;can be compiled to&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/C_(programming_language)" title="C (programming language)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">C</a>, and is used to build the PyPy interpreter of Python.</li></ul><h3 style="font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.6; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 0.3em 0px 0px; font-size: 1.2em; background: none; overflow: hidden; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; border-bottom: 0px;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Performance">Performance</span><span class="mw-editsection" style="user-select: none; font-size: small; font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; white-space: nowrap; unicode-bidi: isolate;"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket" style="margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);">[</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Python_(programming_language)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=18" title="Edit section: Performance" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket" style="margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);">]</span></span></h3><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">A performance comparison of various Python implementations on a non-numerical (combinatorial) workload was presented at EuroSciPy '13.<sup id="cite_ref-121" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-121" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[121]</a></sup>&nbsp;Python's performance compared to other programming languages has also been benchmarked by&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Computer_Language_Benchmarks_Game" title="The Computer Language Benchmarks Game" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">The Computer Language Benchmarks Game</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-122" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-122" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[122]</a></sup></p><h2 style="font-family: &quot;Linux Libertine&quot;, Georgia, Times, serif; line-height: 1.3; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 1em 0px 0.25em; font-size: 1.5em; background: none; overflow: hidden; padding: 0px; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(162, 169, 177);"><span class="mw-headline" id="Development">Development</span><span class="mw-editsection" style="font-family: sans-serif; user-select: none; font-size: small; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; white-space: nowrap; unicode-bidi: isolate;"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket" style="margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);">[</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Python_(programming_language)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=19" title="Edit section: Development" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket" style="margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);">]</span></span></h2><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Python's development is conducted largely through the&nbsp;<i>Python Enhancement Proposal</i>&nbsp;(PEP) process, the primary mechanism for proposing major new features, collecting community input on issues and documenting Python design decisions.<sup id="cite_ref-PepCite000_123-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-PepCite000-123" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[123]</a></sup>&nbsp;Python coding style is covered in PEP 8.<sup id="cite_ref-124" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-124" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[124]</a></sup>&nbsp;Outstanding PEPs are reviewed and commented on by the Python community and the steering council.<sup id="cite_ref-PepCite000_123-1" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-PepCite000-123" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[123]</a></sup></p><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Enhancement of the language corresponds with development of the CPython reference implementation. The mailing list python-dev is the primary forum for the language's development. Specific issues are discussed in the&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roundup_(issue_tracker)" title="Roundup (issue tracker)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Roundup</a>&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bug_tracker" class="mw-redirect" title="Bug tracker" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">bug tracker</a>&nbsp;hosted at&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://bugs.python.org/" style="color: rgb(102, 51, 102); background-image: linear-gradient(transparent, transparent), url(&quot;/w/skins/Vector/resources/skins.vector.styles/images/external-link-ltr-icon.svg?b4b84&quot;); background-position: right center; background-repeat: no-repeat, repeat; padding-right: 13px;">bugs.python.org</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-21_125-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-21-125" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[125]</a></sup>&nbsp;Development originally took place on a&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Self-hosting_(web_services)" title="Self-hosting (web services)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">self-hosted</a>&nbsp;source-code repository running&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mercurial" title="Mercurial" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Mercurial</a>, until Python moved to&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GitHub" title="GitHub" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">GitHub</a>&nbsp;in January 2017.<sup id="cite_ref-py_dev_guide_126-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-py_dev_guide-126" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[126]</a></sup></p><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">CPython's public releases come in three types, distinguished by which part of the version number is incremented:</p><ul style="margin: 0.3em 0px 0px 1.6em; list-style-image: url(&quot;/w/skins/Vector/resources/skins.vector.styles/images/bullet-icon.svg?d4515&quot;); padding: 0px;"><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;">Backward-incompatible versions, where code is expected to break and need to be manually&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ported" class="mw-redirect" title="Ported" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">ported</a>. The first part of the version number is incremented. These releases happen infrequently‚Äîfor example, version 3.0 was released 8 years after 2.0.</li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;">Major or "feature" releases, about every 18 months, are largely compatible but introduce new features. The second part of the version number is incremented. Each major version is supported by bugfixes for several years after its release.<sup id="cite_ref-release-schedule_127-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-release-schedule-127" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[127]</a></sup></li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;">Bugfix releases, which introduce no new features, occur about every 3 months and are made when a sufficient number of bugs have been fixed upstream since the last release. Security vulnerabilities are also patched in these releases. The third and final part of the version number is incremented.<sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-22_128-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-22-128" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[128]</a></sup></li></ul><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Python 3.9 alpha1 was announced in November 2019<sup id="cite_ref-129" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-129" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[129]</a></sup>&nbsp;and with the adoption of a new yearly release cadence,<sup id="cite_ref-130" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-130" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[130]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-131" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-131" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[131]</a></sup>&nbsp;the first release of 3.9 is slated for November 2020.<sup id="cite_ref-132" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-132" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[132]</a></sup></p><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Many&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Beta_release" class="mw-redirect" title="Beta release" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">alpha, beta, and release-candidates</a>&nbsp;are also released as previews and for testing before final releases. Although there is a rough schedule for each release, they are often delayed if the code is not ready. Python's development team monitors the state of the code by running the large&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unit_test" class="mw-redirect" title="Unit test" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">unit test</a>&nbsp;suite during development, and using the&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BuildBot" class="mw-redirect" title="BuildBot" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">BuildBot</a>&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Continuous_integration" title="Continuous integration" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">continuous integration</a>&nbsp;system.<sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-23_133-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-23-133" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[133]</a></sup></p><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">The major&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Academic_conference" title="Academic conference" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">academic conference</a>&nbsp;on Python is&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PyCon" class="mw-redirect" title="PyCon" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">PyCon</a>. There are also special Python mentoring programmes, such as&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pyladies" class="mw-redirect" title="Pyladies" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Pyladies</a>.</p><h2 style="font-family: &quot;Linux Libertine&quot;, Georgia, Times, serif; line-height: 1.3; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 1em 0px 0.25em; font-size: 1.5em; background: none; overflow: hidden; padding: 0px; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(162, 169, 177);"><span class="mw-headline" id="Naming">Naming</span><span class="mw-editsection" style="font-family: sans-serif; user-select: none; font-size: small; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; white-space: nowrap; unicode-bidi: isolate;"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket" style="margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);">[</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Python_(programming_language)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=20" title="Edit section: Naming" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket" style="margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);">]</span></span></h2><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Python's name is derived from the British comedy group&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Monty_Python" title="Monty Python" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Monty Python</a>, whom Python creator Guido van Rossum enjoyed while developing the language. Monty Python references appear frequently in Python code and culture;<sup id="cite_ref-tutorial-chapter1_134-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-tutorial-chapter1-134" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[134]</a></sup>&nbsp;for example, the&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metasyntactic_variable" title="Metasyntactic variable" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">metasyntactic variables</a>&nbsp;often used in Python literature are&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spam_(Monty_Python)" title="Spam (Monty Python)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);"><i>spam</i>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<i>eggs</i></a>&nbsp;instead of the traditional&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Foobar" title="Foobar" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);"><i>foo</i>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<i>bar</i></a>.<sup id="cite_ref-tutorial-chapter1_134-1" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-tutorial-chapter1-134" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[134]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-26_135-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-26-135" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[135]</a></sup>&nbsp;The official Python documentation also contains various references to Monty Python routines.<sup id="cite_ref-136" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-136" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[136]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-137" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-137" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[137]</a></sup></p><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">The prefix&nbsp;<i>Py-</i>&nbsp;is used to show that something is related to Python. Examples of the use of this prefix in names of Python applications or libraries include&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pygame" title="Pygame" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Pygame</a>, a&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Language_binding" title="Language binding" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">binding</a>&nbsp;of&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Simple_DirectMedia_Layer" title="Simple DirectMedia Layer" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">SDL</a>&nbsp;to Python (commonly used to create games);&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PyQt" title="PyQt" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">PyQt</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PyGTK" title="PyGTK" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">PyGTK</a>, which bind&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Qt_(software)" title="Qt (software)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Qt</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GTK" title="GTK" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">GTK</a>&nbsp;to Python respectively; and&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PyPy" title="PyPy" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">PyPy</a>, a Python implementation originally written in Python.</p><h2 style="font-family: &quot;Linux Libertine&quot;, Georgia, Times, serif; line-height: 1.3; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 1em 0px 0.25em; font-size: 1.5em; background: none; overflow: hidden; padding: 0px; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(162, 169, 177);"><span class="mw-headline" id="API_documentation_generators">API documentation generators</span><span class="mw-editsection" style="font-family: sans-serif; user-select: none; font-size: small; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; white-space: nowrap; unicode-bidi: isolate;"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket" style="margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);">[</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Python_(programming_language)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=21" title="Edit section: API documentation generators" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket" style="margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);">]</span></span></h2><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Python API documentation generators include:</p><ul style="margin: 0.3em 0px 0px 1.6em; list-style-image: url(&quot;/w/skins/Vector/resources/skins.vector.styles/images/bullet-icon.svg?d4515&quot;); padding: 0px;"><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Epydoc" title="Epydoc" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Epydoc</a></li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HeaderDoc" title="HeaderDoc" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">HeaderDoc</a></li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pydoc" title="Pydoc" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">pydoc</a></li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sphinx_(documentation_generator)" title="Sphinx (documentation generator)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Sphinx</a></li></ul><h2 style="font-family: &quot;Linux Libertine&quot;, Georgia, Times, serif; line-height: 1.3; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 1em 0px 0.25em; font-size: 1.5em; background: none; overflow: hidden; padding: 0px; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(162, 169, 177);"><span class="mw-headline" id="Uses">Uses</span><span class="mw-editsection" style="font-family: sans-serif; user-select: none; font-size: small; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; white-space: nowrap; unicode-bidi: isolate;"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket" style="margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);">[</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Python_(programming_language)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=22" title="Edit section: Uses" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket" style="margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);">]</span></span></h2><div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable" style="font-style: italic; padding-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Main article:&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Python_software" title="List of Python software" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">List of Python software</a></div><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Since 2003, Python has consistently ranked in the top ten most popular programming languages in the&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TIOBE_Programming_Community_Index" class="mw-redirect" title="TIOBE Programming Community Index" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">TIOBE Programming Community Index</a>&nbsp;where, as of February&nbsp;2020, it is the third most popular language (behind&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Java_(programming_language)" title="Java (programming language)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Java</a>, and&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/C_(programming_language)" title="C (programming language)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">C</a>).<sup id="cite_ref-138" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-138" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[138]</a></sup>&nbsp;It was selected Programming Language of the Year in 2007, 2010, and 2018.<sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-34_139-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-34-139" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[139]</a></sup></p><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">An empirical study found that scripting languages, such as Python, are more productive than conventional languages, such as C and Java, for programming problems involving string manipulation and search in a dictionary, and determined that memory consumption was often "better than Java and not much worse than C or C++".<sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-28_140-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-28-140" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[140]</a></sup></p><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Large organizations that use Python include&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia" title="Wikipedia" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Wikipedia</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Google" title="Google" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Google</a>,<sup id="cite_ref-quotes-about-python_141-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-quotes-about-python-141" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[141]</a></sup>&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yahoo!" title="Yahoo!" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Yahoo!</a>,<sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-29_142-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-29-142" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[142]</a></sup>&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CERN" title="CERN" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">CERN</a>,<sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-30_143-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-30-143" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[143]</a></sup>&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NASA" title="NASA" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">NASA</a>,<sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-31_144-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-31-144" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[144]</a></sup>&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Facebook" title="Facebook" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Facebook</a>,<sup id="cite_ref-145" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-145" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[145]</a></sup>&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amazon_(company)" title="Amazon (company)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Amazon</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Instagram" title="Instagram" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Instagram</a>,<sup id="cite_ref-146" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-146" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[146]</a></sup>&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spotify" title="Spotify" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Spotify</a><sup id="cite_ref-147" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-147" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[147]</a></sup>&nbsp;and some smaller entities like&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Industrial_Light_%26_Magic" title="Industrial Light &amp; Magic" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">ILM</a><sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-32_148-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-32-148" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[148]</a></sup>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ITA_Software" title="ITA Software" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">ITA</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-33_149-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-33-149" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[149]</a></sup>&nbsp;The social news networking site&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reddit" title="Reddit" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Reddit</a>&nbsp;is written entirely in Python.<sup id="cite_ref-150" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-150" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[150]</a></sup></p><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Python can serve as a&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scripting_language" title="Scripting language" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">scripting language</a>&nbsp;for&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Web_application" title="Web application" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">web applications</a>, e.g., via&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mod_wsgi" title="Mod wsgi" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">mod_wsgi</a>&nbsp;for the&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Apache_web_server" class="mw-redirect" title="Apache web server" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Apache web server</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-35_151-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-35-151" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[151]</a></sup>&nbsp;With&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Web_Server_Gateway_Interface" title="Web Server Gateway Interface" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Web Server Gateway Interface</a>, a standard API has evolved to facilitate these applications.&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Web_framework" title="Web framework" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Web frameworks</a>&nbsp;like&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Django_(web_framework)" title="Django (web framework)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Django</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pylons_(web_framework)" class="mw-redirect" title="Pylons (web framework)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Pylons</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pyramid_(web_framework)" class="mw-redirect" title="Pyramid (web framework)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Pyramid</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TurboGears" title="TurboGears" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">TurboGears</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Web2py" title="Web2py" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">web2py</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tornado_(web_server)" title="Tornado (web server)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Tornado</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flask_(web_framework)" title="Flask (web framework)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Flask</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bottle_(web_framework)" title="Bottle (web framework)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Bottle</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zope" title="Zope" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Zope</a>&nbsp;support developers in the design and maintenance of complex applications.&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pyjs" title="Pyjs" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Pyjs</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IronPython" title="IronPython" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">IronPython</a>&nbsp;can be used to develop the client-side of Ajax-based applications.&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SQLAlchemy" title="SQLAlchemy" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">SQLAlchemy</a>&nbsp;can be used as&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Data_mapper_pattern" title="Data mapper pattern" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">data mapper</a>&nbsp;to a relational database.&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Twisted_(software)" title="Twisted (software)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Twisted</a>&nbsp;is a framework to program communications between computers, and is used (for example) by&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dropbox_(service)" title="Dropbox (service)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Dropbox</a>.</p><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Libraries such as&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NumPy" title="NumPy" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">NumPy</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SciPy" title="SciPy" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">SciPy</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Matplotlib" title="Matplotlib" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Matplotlib</a>&nbsp;allow the effective use of Python in&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scientific_computing" class="mw-redirect" title="Scientific computing" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">scientific computing</a>,<sup id="cite_ref-cise_152-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-cise-152" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[152]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-millman_153-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-millman-153" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[153]</a></sup>&nbsp;with specialized libraries such as&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Biopython" title="Biopython" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Biopython</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Astropy" title="Astropy" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Astropy</a>&nbsp;providing domain-specific functionality.&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SageMath" title="SageMath" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">SageMath</a>&nbsp;is a&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematical_software" title="Mathematical software" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">mathematical software</a>&nbsp;with a&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Notebook_interface" title="Notebook interface" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">notebook interface</a>&nbsp;programmable in Python: its library covers many aspects of&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematics" title="Mathematics" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">mathematics</a>, including&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Algebra" title="Algebra" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">algebra</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Combinatorics" title="Combinatorics" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">combinatorics</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Numerical_mathematics" class="mw-redirect" title="Numerical mathematics" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">numerical mathematics</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Number_theory" title="Number theory" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">number theory</a>, and&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Calculus" title="Calculus" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">calculus</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-ICSE_154-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-ICSE-154" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[154]</a></sup></p><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Python has been successfully embedded in many software products as a scripting language, including in&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Finite_element_method" title="Finite element method" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">finite element method</a>&nbsp;software such as&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abaqus" title="Abaqus" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Abaqus</a>, 3D parametric modeler like&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FreeCAD" title="FreeCAD" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">FreeCAD</a>, 3D animation packages such as&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/3ds_Max" class="mw-redirect" title="3ds Max" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">3ds Max</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blender_(software)" title="Blender (software)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Blender</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cinema_4D" title="Cinema 4D" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Cinema 4D</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lightwave" class="mw-redirect" title="Lightwave" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Lightwave</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Houdini_(software)" title="Houdini (software)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Houdini</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maya_(software)" class="mw-redirect" title="Maya (software)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Maya</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Modo_(software)" title="Modo (software)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">modo</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MotionBuilder" class="mw-redirect" title="MotionBuilder" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">MotionBuilder</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Autodesk_Softimage" title="Autodesk Softimage" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Softimage</a>, the visual effects compositor&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nuke_(software)" title="Nuke (software)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Nuke</a>, 2D imaging programs like&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GIMP" title="GIMP" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">GIMP</a>,<sup id="cite_ref-155" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-155" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[155]</a></sup>&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inkscape" title="Inkscape" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Inkscape</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scribus" title="Scribus" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Scribus</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paint_Shop_Pro" class="mw-redirect" title="Paint Shop Pro" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Paint Shop Pro</a>,<sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-38_156-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-38-156" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[156]</a></sup>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Musical_notation" title="Musical notation" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">musical notation</a>&nbsp;programs like&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scorewriter" title="Scorewriter" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">scorewriter</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Capella_(notation_program)" title="Capella (notation program)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">capella</a>.&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GNU_Debugger" title="GNU Debugger" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">GNU Debugger</a>&nbsp;uses Python as a&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prettyprint" title="Prettyprint" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">pretty printer</a>&nbsp;to show complex structures such as C++ containers.&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Esri" title="Esri" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Esri</a>&nbsp;promotes Python as the best choice for writing scripts in&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ArcGIS" title="ArcGIS" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">ArcGIS</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-39_157-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-39-157" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[157]</a></sup>&nbsp;It has also been used in several video games,<sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-40_158-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-40-158" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[158]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-41_159-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-41-159" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[159]</a></sup>&nbsp;and has been adopted as first of the three available&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Programming_language" title="Programming language" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">programming languages</a>&nbsp;in&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Google_App_Engine" title="Google App Engine" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Google App Engine</a>, the other two being&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Java_(software_platform)" title="Java (software platform)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Java</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Go_(programming_language)" title="Go (programming language)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Go</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-42_160-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-42-160" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[160]</a></sup></p><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Python is commonly used in&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Artificial_intelligence" title="Artificial intelligence" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">artificial intelligence</a>&nbsp;projects and machine learning projects with the help of libraries like&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TensorFlow" title="TensorFlow" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">TensorFlow</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Keras" title="Keras" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Keras</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PyTorch" title="PyTorch" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Pytorch</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scikit-learn" title="Scikit-learn" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Scikit-learn</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-whitepaper2015_161-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-whitepaper2015-161" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[161]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-162" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-162" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[162]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-163" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-163" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[163]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-164" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-164" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[164]</a></sup>&nbsp;As a scripting language with&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Modular_programming" title="Modular programming" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">modular architecture</a>, simple syntax and rich text processing tools, Python is often used for&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Natural_language_processing" title="Natural language processing" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">natural language processing</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-47_165-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-47-165" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[165]</a></sup></p><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Many operating systems include Python as a standard component. It ships with most&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linux_distribution" title="Linux distribution" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Linux distributions</a>,<sup id="cite_ref-166" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-166" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[166]</a></sup>&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/AmigaOS_4" title="AmigaOS 4" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">AmigaOS 4</a>&nbsp;(using Python 2.7),&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FreeBSD" title="FreeBSD" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">FreeBSD</a>&nbsp;(as a package),&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NetBSD" title="NetBSD" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">NetBSD</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OpenBSD" title="OpenBSD" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">OpenBSD</a>&nbsp;(as a package) and&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MacOS" title="MacOS" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">macOS</a>&nbsp;and can be used from the command line (terminal). Many Linux distributions use installers written in Python:&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ubuntu_(operating_system)" class="mw-redirect" title="Ubuntu (operating system)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Ubuntu</a>&nbsp;uses the&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ubiquity_(software)" title="Ubiquity (software)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Ubiquity</a>&nbsp;installer, while&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Red_Hat_Linux" title="Red Hat Linux" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Red Hat Linux</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fedora_(operating_system)" title="Fedora (operating system)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Fedora</a>&nbsp;use the&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anaconda_(installer)" title="Anaconda (installer)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Anaconda</a>&nbsp;installer.&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gentoo_Linux" title="Gentoo Linux" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Gentoo Linux</a>&nbsp;uses Python in its&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Package_management_system" class="mw-redirect" title="Package management system" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">package management system</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Portage_(software)" title="Portage (software)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Portage</a>.</p><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Python is used extensively in the&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Information_security" title="Information security" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">information security</a>&nbsp;industry, including in exploit development.<sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-49_167-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-49-167" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[167]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-50_168-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-50-168" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[168]</a></sup></p><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Most of the&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sugar_(software)" title="Sugar (software)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Sugar</a>&nbsp;software for the&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/One_Laptop_per_Child" title="One Laptop per Child" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">One Laptop per Child</a>&nbsp;XO, now developed at&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sugar_Labs" title="Sugar Labs" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Sugar Labs</a>, is written in Python.<sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-51_169-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-51-169" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[169]</a></sup>&nbsp;The&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Raspberry_Pi" title="Raspberry Pi" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Raspberry Pi</a>&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Single-board_computer" title="Single-board computer" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">single-board computer</a>&nbsp;project has adopted Python as its main user-programming language.</p><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Due to Python's user-friendly conventions and easy-to-understand language, it is commonly used as an intro language into computing sciences with students.<sup class="noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; white-space: nowrap;">[<i><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources. (April 2020)">citation needed</span></a></i>]</sup></p><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LibreOffice" title="LibreOffice" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">LibreOffice</a>&nbsp;includes Python, and intends to replace Java with Python. Its Python Scripting Provider is a core feature<sup id="cite_ref-170" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-170" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[170]</a></sup>&nbsp;since Version 4.0 from 7 February 2013.</p><h2 style="font-family: &quot;Linux Libertine&quot;, Georgia, Times, serif; line-height: 1.3; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin: 1em 0px 0.25em; font-size: 1.5em; background: none; overflow: hidden; padding: 0px; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(162, 169, 177);"><span class="mw-headline" id="Languages_influenced_by_Python">Languages influenced by Python</span><span class="mw-editsection" style="font-family: sans-serif; user-select: none; font-size: small; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; white-space: nowrap; unicode-bidi: isolate;"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket" style="margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);">[</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Python_(programming_language)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=23" title="Edit section: Languages influenced by Python" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket" style="margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);">]</span></span></h2><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Python's design and philosophy have influenced many other programming languages:</p><ul style="margin: 0.3em 0px 0px 1.6em; list-style-image: url(&quot;/w/skins/Vector/resources/skins.vector.styles/images/bullet-icon.svg?d4515&quot;); padding: 0px;"><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boo_(programming_language)" title="Boo (programming language)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Boo</a>&nbsp;uses indentation, a similar syntax, and a similar object model.<sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-90_171-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-90-171" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[171]</a></sup></li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cobra_(programming_language)" title="Cobra (programming language)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Cobra</a>&nbsp;uses indentation and a similar syntax, and its&nbsp;<i>Acknowledgements</i>&nbsp;document lists Python first among languages that influenced it.<sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-91_172-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-91-172" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[172]</a></sup></li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CoffeeScript" title="CoffeeScript" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">CoffeeScript</a>, a&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Programming_language" title="Programming language" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">programming language</a>&nbsp;that cross-compiles to JavaScript, has Python-inspired syntax.</li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ECMAScript" title="ECMAScript" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">ECMAScript</a>/<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/JavaScript" title="JavaScript" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">JavaScript</a>&nbsp;borrowed&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iterator" title="Iterator" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">iterators</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Generator_(computer_science)" class="mw-redirect" title="Generator (computer science)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">generators</a>&nbsp;from Python.<sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-93_173-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-93-173" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[173]</a></sup></li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GDScript" class="mw-redirect" title="GDScript" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">GDScript</a>, a scripting language very similar to Python, built-in to the&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Godot_(game_engine)" title="Godot (game engine)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Godot</a>&nbsp;game engine.<sup id="cite_ref-174" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-174" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[174]</a></sup></li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Go_(programming_language)" title="Go (programming language)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Go</a>&nbsp;is designed for the "speed of working in a dynamic language like Python"<sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-94_175-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-94-175" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[175]</a></sup>&nbsp;and shares the same syntax for slicing arrays.</li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Groovy_(programming_language)" class="mw-redirect" title="Groovy (programming language)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Groovy</a>&nbsp;was motivated by the desire to bring the Python design philosophy to&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Java_(programming_language)" title="Java (programming language)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Java</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-95_176-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-95-176" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[176]</a></sup></li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Julia_(programming_language)" title="Julia (programming language)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Julia</a>&nbsp;was designed to be "as usable for general programming as Python".<sup id="cite_ref-Julia_24-1" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-Julia-24" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[24]</a></sup></li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nim_(programming_language)" title="Nim (programming language)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Nim</a>&nbsp;uses indentation and a similar syntax.<sup class="noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; white-space: nowrap;">[<i><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources. (February 2020)">citation needed</span></a></i>]</sup></li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ruby_(programming_language)" title="Ruby (programming language)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Ruby</a>'s creator,&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yukihiro_Matsumoto" title="Yukihiro Matsumoto" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Yukihiro Matsumoto</a>, has said: "I wanted a scripting language that was more powerful than Perl, and more object-oriented than Python. That's why I decided to design my own language."<sup id="cite_ref-linuxdevcenter_177-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-linuxdevcenter-177" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[177]</a></sup></li><li style="margin-bottom: 0.1em;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swift_(programming_language)" title="Swift (programming language)" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Swift</a>, a programming language developed by Apple, has some Python-inspired syntax.<sup id="cite_ref-178" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-178" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">[178]</a></sup></li></ul><p style="margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Python's development practices have also been emulated by other languages. For example, the practice of requiring a document describing the rationale for, and issues surrounding, a change to the language (in Python, a PEP) is also used in&nbsp;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tcl" title="Tcl" style="background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Tcl</a>,<sup id="cite_ref-AutoNT-99_179-0" class="reference" style="font-size: 11.2px; line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)#cite_note-AutoNT-99-179" style="background-image: none; background-